				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Auging the Epic<a name="40784"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 19 04 2:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Put procs on your weapons. This has given my melee DPS a dramatic boost. I put the 150 cold DD proc on my epic. It doesn't land much in PoWater, but elsewhere it seems to land just fine. I have the 125 poison based proc added to my main hand, which already has a 160 fire based proc on it (LIB).
<br />

<br />
I also have WA5 and Spell Casting Fury (procs land for double about 7% of the time). With that set up I find that in a one minute fight it is not unusual for me to land 9 to 11 procs, and almost one in ten is a crit. My rough estimates are that I am doing around 1000 to 1500 more damage with that set up per minute. I don't know many other ways a bard can up his melee dps by 18 to 25 or so.
<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
65 Bard of Torv </span></td>
